================================================================
STANDARD GNN BASELINE — 3-sine-wave toy problem (gCTLN contrast)
================================================================

Architecture:
  (1) FeedforwardGNN — t as input, no temporal recurrence
  (2) RecurrentGNN   — learned neural ODE on 3-cycle graph
  Shared MPLayer: MLP(concat src,dst) → sum-aggregate → MLP update

Task: fit three non-negative sines at 120° phase offsets
      x_i(t) = 0.4·sin(t + i·2π/3) + 0.5   on a 3-cycle graph

Purpose: show vanilla GNNs struggle with sustained oscillations,
         exposing the inductive-bias advantage of gCTLNs.
================================================================

Configuration:
  Script:   scripts/gnn_baseline.py
  Output:   /scratch/xfd3tf/gnn_sine_baseline
  Device:   CPU (problem is tiny — 3 nodes, 1k timesteps)
  Threads:  4
================================================================

